This paper is about reading comprehension, which is a natural language processing task. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses a state-of-the-art RC model, which involves neural networks and reinforcement learning, indicating that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves attention mechanisms, which are commonly used in neural networks for natural language processing, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper uses datasets that involve text and may require visual understanding, indicating that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision).
